				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				hi all,<BR>
  I'm a lvl 16 wood elf druid on the Luclin server.  I don't want to be offensive, but i have to agree with those who say &quot;no&quot; to melee as a druid.  I had stopped melee with anything unless forced to at lvl 10.  i found my favorite way to hunt is to cast your root spell, then DOT, then back up from your foe and sit down and med.  Await the warning in the chat screen telling you your spell has run its course, and then recast said spell.  Be careful though!! if your skill for your root spell is low, it will break more often.  The reason I tell you to root instead of snare is the fact that the DOT will do more damage if the Mob is stuck in place, and although it takes longer, your DOT's will do more damage/mana than DD, or AoE.  Take care of yourselves, and remember to stay SoWed just in case the tide of battle goes bad.<BR>
<BR>
