				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I just have to respond to the post about Druids being able to melee.  ARE YOU INSANE!  I have a level 39 Druid.  I do not melee unless I have the badie snared and he is down to a sliver of health and I decide I do not want to waste mana on him.  My melee skill in 1HB is 150.  Even still, if I decide to root that badie with the same sliver of health and melee him, I will lose two bubbles of health in the sliver I pound off of him.<BR>
<BR>
If I use all of my BUF's (Firefist, Strength, Greater Wolf, Skin spells, Regen, and Shield spell), I could not deal out enough damage to a Green creature (including a Harrier which has been green for about 8 levels now) in melee.  First off, we just do not have the AC or HP to stand up in melee.  That is just a fact and the way it is.  Secondly, if I choose to find the best melee weapon I can find for my class, I lose out on any WIS stats that the others give me and I still can not hit often enough to make a difference.<BR>
<BR>
I still do not do max damage now on high Greens most of the time and hit only about 50% of the time on a great day when all of the stars are aligned and I win the lottery...  It just does not happen.  It will never happen and a Druids lot in life is to be a Bus who can burn a little, BUF a little, DOT a little, heal a little, etc.  We are kiting fools who can solo almost indefinately.  We will never be the primary anything, but a great all around utility member to any group as well as Bus driver to get around and Evac out of bad situations.<BR>
<BR>
Melee!?!  That is just a bad joke!<BR>
<BR>
Snydarea Mystwalker<BR>

